Subject: Re: [AlwaysLearning] was here's the best one yet



In a message dated 8/14/03 4:40:25 AM, kbcdlovejo@... writes:

<< For future reference, MOST of Deb's posts are-----um....humorous?

Well, unless she's MAD! >>

I think it's funny when she's mad.

And for future reference, it's my list, so if I want to pick on somebody I
can.
Nobody's paying me to run this list, there's no board of directors, it's just
like one of those CRAZY little independent filling stations that can charge
too much for gas, sell whatever weird stuff they want at the counter, has the
TV blasting and some benches for people to hang out.

You COULD go to the big Texaco on the corner where they have exactly what the
corporation told them to have on the shelves in the very corporate places, or
you can hang out and take your chances on what's TV here.

People learn more at the independent place than the "what town or street
corner is THIS one on?" shop.

Sandra
